ity, which is absolutely the priority,\\\" Tony Estanguet, president of the Paris 2024 organising committee, told a press conference on Sunday.\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1394, \"end\": 1408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 1427, \"end\": 1437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1768561406776544e-16, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a balance\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1324}, {\"ngram\": \"top security\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1357}, {\"ngram\": \"absolutely the priority\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1391}, {\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1419}, {\"ngram\": \"a press conference\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1483}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1493}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's part of the objective to guarantee the security and to propose a fantastic celebration of the Games...\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1604, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1502, \"to\": 1506}, {\"ngram\": \"the objective\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1523}, {\"ngram\": \"the security\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1549}, {\"ngram\": \"a fantastic celebration\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1588}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1601}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But to have this kind of unique celebration, you also need to have a very, very strong security plan.\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1706, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this kind\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1626}, {\"ngram\": \"unique celebration\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1648}, {\"ngram\": \"a very, very strong security plan\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1705}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's the case.\\\"\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1728, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony, which will start at 7:30 p.m. local time(1730 GMT), will be \\\"a large fresco\\\" celebrating Paris, France and the Games and will interweave the traditional parade by athletes with artistic performances and elements of protocol, said Thomas Jolly, the artistic director of the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 2034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1790, \"end\": 1793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.732139370196735e-15, \"text\": \"GMT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greenwich_Mean_Time\"}, {\"begin\": 1833, \"end\": 1838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.093294937215571e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1840, \"end\": 1846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9998714712342447, \"rank\": 8.060290293259462e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1974, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.6830955000928979, \"rank\": 0.44525835620304954, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ceremony